history.content: Last semester (I'm a sophomore) I took 61C, 120, and EECS 149; another popular combination among my classmates was 61C+120+170. I found 120 to be pretty light workload, and it's also generally a very useful class. Very different from 61C so they complement each other well. I can't speak to 168, but I've heard it's not *that* bad, so that sounds like a good workload!
